descript.abstract: This parcel layer contains discrete, non-overlapping polygons for each property. Adjacent polygons with common ownership and a single tax record have been retained in the "OthLeg" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer, and dissolved into single parcels in this TaxPar layer. Some non-adjacent parcels may be represented by multi-part polygons where they share common ownership and a single tax record. Public right of ways exist as polygons, not null space. Linework associated with private ROWs are retained in the "OthLeg" layer. Water polygons also representing parcel boundaries have been retained in this TaxPar layer. Additional water features that are not considered parcel boundaries may have been placed in the "Misc" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer. Easements and other similar non-fee taxable boundaries exist in the 'OthLeg" layer, not the TaxPar layer.Credits Geometry and attribute data updated based on source information provided by Assessor June 2018

That work requires a licensed land surveyor.

procstep.procdesc: Existing digital data fit to an orthophoto base. Parcel lines were modified to fit ground features in some instances. Quality checks applied, such as topology checks for gaps, overlaps for features in the newly created digital dataset. Relationship between the parcel fabric and assessor table performed. Any discrepancies were delivered to the assessor, all were resolved.
Parcel geometry and attributes were updated based on information provided by Assessor

CAMA data was matched against parcel data to produce a mismatch report which was reconciled with the help of the town. final QAQC tool was run.
